Parse forms in a page.

Source: R/form.R
html_form.Rd

Parse forms in a page.

html_form(x)

Arguments

x

A node, node set or document.

See also

HTML 4.01 form specification: http://www.w3.org/TR/html401/interact/forms.html

Examples

html_form(read_html("https://hadley.wufoo.com/forms/libraryrequire-quiz/"))
#> [[1]]
#> <form> 'form27' (POST https://hadley.wufoo.com/forms/libraryrequire-quiz/)
#>   <input hidden> 'Field1': 
#>   <input radio> 'Field1': Loads the class package
#>   <input radio> 'Field1': Loads the cluster package
#>   <input radio> 'Field1': I have no idea!
#>   <input radio> 'Field1': Something else
#>   <input text> 'Field1_other_Something else': 
#>   <input hidden> 'currentPage': GfqNaMDZduwwhzuA9YxErPxIPfa0GJOeczQWDlLzZzI=
#>   <input submit> 'saveForm': Submit
#>   <textarea> 'comment' [0 char]
#>   <input hidden> 'idstamp': K2usAn/awmxbltuyp6a77nxaxkLBqab+50PUZHtuuMI=
#>   <input hidden> 'stats': {"errors":0,"startTime":0,"endTime":0,"referer":null}

box_office <- read_html("http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=ateam.htm")
box_office %>% html_node("form") %>% html_form()
#> <form> 'searchbox' (POST /search/q.php)
#>   <input text> 'q': 
#>   <input submit> '': Search...
